# Visionary Design System

Source of truth: `docs/design.md` (frozen). Do not modify the spec unless explicitly requested.

## Token Layers

Follow **Primitive → Semantic → Component → Theme** only. Tokens flow downward.

| Layer | Use in product UI |
| --- | --- |
| Semantic / Component | Yes — default for all UI |
| Theme overrides | Yes — one theme per product surface |
| Primitive | No — definitions and token files only |

**Required chain:** Product UI → Theme (if active) → Component token → Semantic token → Primitive.

## Forbidden in Product UI

Never hardcode or invent values outside the spec:

- Hex/rgb/hsl colors (including `#`, `rgba(`)
- Spacing (e.g. `13px`, `margin: 20px` unless mapped to `spacing.*`)
- Radius (use `radius.sm|md|lg|xl|pill` only)
- Shadows (use `elevation.card|dropdown|modal` only)
- Typography (use `typography.*` scale — no raw `font-size`, `line-height`, `letter-spacing`, or font-family)
- Z-index (use `elevation.*.z-index` or `elevation.overlay` only)
- Motion durations/easing (use `motion.duration.*` and `motion.easing.*`)

## Semantic Tokens (required roles)

Use named tokens from `docs/design.md`, not palette steps:

- Surfaces: `background.*`, `surface.*`
- Text: `text.primary|secondary|muted|inverse|on-solid`
- Actions: `action.primary*|accent*|destructive*`
- Status: `status.{success|warning|error|info}.*`
- Interaction: `focus.*`, `disabled.*`, `link.*`, `overlay.scrim*`

## Component Tokens

Button, Input, Card, Alert, and Modal must consume **component token slots** defined in `docs/design.md`. Component tokens reference semantic tokens only — never primitives.

## Foundations

- New shadows, breakpoints, spacing steps, or radius values require spec approval first.
- No product-specific names in primitive or semantic token keys.
- Do not use opacity hacks instead of `disabled.*` tokens.
